id: pm-dijg
title: "Schema evolution migrations: lossless, history-recorded bulk migration of existing items when custom types, fields, or statuses are renamed or retired"
description: "Provide SDK-first, dry-run-first, resumable schema evolution migrations that losslessly rename or retire types, fields, and statuses with immutable audit proof."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 2
tags[5]: customization,durability,long-horizon,schema,sdk
created_at: "2026-07-06T23:35:40.341Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-13T21:37:56.466Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 720
acceptance_criteria: "pm schema gains migration verbs (SDK-first): rename-type, rename-field, remap-status/retire-status with an explicit value mapping; a --dry-run plan enumerates affected items and per-field changes before any write; execution rewrites affected items losslessly (unknown/unmapped values are never silently dropped) and appends a migration history entry to every touched item plus the workspace stream, preserving immutable proof; migration is O(affected) via the derived read index at 100k+ scale (benchmark on pm-mi2x workspaces); interrupted migrations are resumable or atomic per item with a verifiable completion check; docs cover the schema-evolution workflow end to end"
parent: pm-8jdc
risk: medium
confidence: medium
